         <abstract>
            <p>A quadrature rule is presented that is exact for integrands of the form π(ξ) + ϖ (ξ) log ξ on the interval (0, 1), where π and ϖ are polynomials. The computed weights and abscissae are given for one- through seven-point rules. In particular, the four-point rule is exact for integral operators with logarithmically singular kernel on a cubic B-spline basis, and it is expected these results shall prove useful for numerical applications of weighted-residual finite element methods.</p>
          </abstract>
